For example:

``` javascript
class GATracking extends React.Component {

    static propTypes = {
        children: PropTypes.node.isRequired,
    }

    static contextTypes = {
        location: locationPropType.isRequired,
    }

    componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState, prevContext) {
        const {location} = this.context
        if (location !== prevContext.location) {
            // Set the tracker to the current page so it is set for other events
            // See: https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/analyticsjs/single-page-applications
            typeof window.ga === 'function' && window.ga('set', 'page', location.pathname + location.search)
            // Signal page view
            typeof window.ga === 'function' && window.ga('send', 'pageview')
        }
    }

    render() {
        return this.props.children
    }
}
```

You can't wrap a v4 `<BrowserRouter>` with such a component.
